cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with in-network stream-processing applications.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of polynomial-time heuristics for operator mapping.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with resource allocation for multiple concurrent applications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with steady-state operation of operator trees.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses quantitative comparisons of different heuristics in simulation.
